Heat 3 tablespoons oil in large skillet over high heat. Sprinkle scallops with pepper blend and salt. Working in batches, add scallops to skillet in single layer; saut√© until brown on outside and just opaque in center, about 2 minutes per side. Transfer scallops to plate, leaving drippings in pan. Add garlic and remaining oil to drippings in skillet; stir 30 seconds. Add orange juice, soy sauce, and orange peel. Boil until sauce thickens to syrup, stirring frequently, about 2 minutes. Pour sauce over scallops and serve.